name: Amazon S3
description: Add an Amazon S3 Instance to connect your existing Amazon S3 account to the Documents Hub, allowing you to manage files and folders as you do with our other Elements. You will need your Amazon S3 account information to add an instance.
configDescription: If you do not have an Amazon AWS account, you can create one at Amazon AWS Signup

configuration.name: Allow Select Fields parameter
configuration.description: Enables use of global fields query parameter to filter response to only specified fields. This will override any existing vendor functionality on the connector

configuration.name: Filter null values from the response
configuration.description: Used to enable/disable filtering of null values from the responses.

configuration.name: Default select fields
configuration.description: Generic map used to specify default fields for bulk download and GET /all requests. Each key should be the canonical objectName and values may be specified as a comma-delimited string or a list of strings

resources.description: Deletes a file from your cloud service by its specified path.

parameters.name: path
parameters.description: The full path to the file (e.g. /myDirectory/myFile.txt)

parameters.name: emptyTrash
parameters.description: Whether or not the trash should be emptied

resources.description: Retrieves a single file from your cloud service from a specified path. The file is directly streamed from the cloud storage provider through Cloud Elements, and is not buffered to disk.

parameters.name: path
parameters.description: The full path to the file (e.g. /myDirectory/myFile.txt)

resources.description: Uploads a file to your endpoint cloud service. If the destination path includes directories that do not exist, they will be created.

parameters.name: file
parameters.description: The file to be uploaded

parameters.name: path
parameters.description: The full path to the file (e.g. /myDirectory/myFile.txt)

parameters.name: size
parameters.description: The size of the file in bytes (required only for SharePoint)

parameters.name: tags[]
parameters.description: Tags associated with the file

parameters.name: description
parameters.description: Description of the file

parameters.name: overwrite
parameters.description: Overwrite the file if the file exists

resources.description: Copies a file specified by a file path to another file path, leaving the original intact.  If the source file path does not exist an error response is returned.  If the destination path includes directories that do not exist, they will be created.  Copying a file that already exists results in an error response.

parameters.name: path
parameters.description: The full path to the file (e.g. /myDirectory/myFile.txt)

parameters.name: body
parameters.description: A CloudFile object representing the destination file. Path is required and no other fields are supported.

resources.description: Deletes a specific file associated with an ID from your cloud service using its specified path.

parameters.name: id
parameters.description: The file ID. For Sharepoint and Dropbox, this is the double URL-encoded path of the file. In this case, the ID must still be URL-encoded on the request, either automatically (e.g. Swagger), or programmatically if the client doesn't take care of it.

parameters.name: emptyTrash
parameters.description: Whether or not the trash should be emptied

resources.description: Retrieves a specific file associated with an ID from your cloud service from a specified path.  The file is directly streamed from the cloud storage provider through Cloud Elements, and is not buffered to disk.

parameters.name: id
parameters.description: The file ID. For Sharepoint and Dropbox, this is the double URL-encoded path of the file. In this case, the ID must still be URL-encoded on the request, either automatically (e.g. Swagger), or programmatically if the client doesn't take care of it.

resources.description: Copies a file associated with an ID from a specified file path to another file path, leaving the original intact. Copying a file that already exists results in an error response.

parameters.description: The file ID. For Sharepoint and Dropbox, this is the double URL-encoded path of the file. In this case, the ID must still be URL-encoded on the request, either automatically (e.g. Swagger), or programmatically if the client doesn't take care of it.

parameters.name: body
parameters.description: A CloudFile object representing the destination file. Path is required

resources.description: Retrieves specific metadata on a file associated with an ID from your cloud service using its specified path.

parameters.name: id
parameters.description: The file ID. For Sharepoint and Dropbox, this is the double URL-encoded path of the file. In this case, the ID must still be URL-encoded on the request, either automatically (e.g. Swagger), or programmatically if the client doesn't take care of it.

parameters.name: isoDates
parameters.description: Optional query parameter to return the created and modified date/time in ISO8601 format.

resources.description: Update a file's metadata (tags and path) associated with an ID.  For example, if you had a document that was tagged as operations but needed to be tagged as legal, then you would perform a PATCH to update the tag using the tags JSON array field. The PATCH method can update the name or directory of a file as well as move a file by using the path JSON field. You cannot update the size of a file.

parameters.name: id
parameters.description: The file ID. For Sharepoint and Dropbox, this is the double URL-encoded path of the file. In this case, the ID must still be URL-encoded on the request, either automatically (e.g. Swagger), or programmatically if the client doesn't take care of it.

parameters.name: body
parameters.description: A Metadata object with the fields to update. Valid values include path and tags

resources.description: Ping the Element to confirm that the Hub element has a heartbeat.  If the Element does not have a heartbeat, an error message will be returned.

Performs a text search of file names and directory names.  The content of files is not searched.  The search uses substring matching so searching for "exam" will match on "example.txt".  Subdirectories are also searched.  The search returns a list of CloudFiles that match search parameters.

parameters.name: path
parameters.description: The full path to the folder to start searching from (e.g. /myDirectory)

parameters.name: text
parameters.description: Text in the file or folder name

parameters.name: startDate
parameters.description: The start date (based on the created date of the file or folder) if used, end date is required

parameters.name: endDate
parameters.description: The end date (based on the created date of the file or folder) if used, start date is required

parameters.name: tags[]
parameters.description: Any tags associated with the files (not applicable to folders)

parameters.name: pageSize
parameters.description: The page size for pagination, which defaults to 200 if not supplied

parameters.name: page
parameters.description: The start page for pagination, which defaults to 1 if not supplied
